Kennedy County was named in honour of the explorer Edmund Besley Court Kennedy (1818-1848).
Kennedy County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located to the west of the Bogan River in the area around Tottenham and Tullamore .
